snippet.textDisplay:
I am not sure if anyone also have this feel but nowadays the coke studio is losing it's touch. Coke studio is known for it's folk music fusion with transitional instruments and pure music without autotune or much post processing. But now a days it feels like another commerical song.

If I compare it with 5-6 years ago cock studio it's not giving that vibe anymore.

snippet.textDisplay:
'The Sunidi Chauhan' can never be replaced or copied. Those of the likes of Ms. Kakkar who try way too hard to get that Vibe are pure disappointment as they always fall flat. Loved this song and way Sunidhi gelled along with the Performers without taking her own spot and limelight Showing off her dress or anything. 
Absolutely disliked the song Ms. Kakkar Did with Coke Studio. The song would have been way better with just the regional singers and not her in it.
